<h6 class="kicker"><a href="//dealbook.blogs.nytimes.com/category/legal/">LEGAL/REGULATORY &#187;</a></h6>
<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><img width="75" height="75" border="0" alt="Ex-Citigroup Manager Cleared in Suit" src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2012/08/01/business/dbpix-citi/dbpix-citi-thumbStandard.jpg"/><span class="title">Ex-Citigroup Manager Cleared in Suit <span class="divider">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span></span><!-- end .title --> The Securities and Exchange Commission lost its lawsuit against Brian Stoker, who was accused of negligence in preparing sales materials for a complex mortgage-related investment.<br /><span class="elsewhere"><a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2012/07/31/former-citigroup-manager-cleared-in-mortgage-securities-case/">DealBook &#187;</a></span><span class="divider">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span><span class="elsewhere"><a href="//www.nytimes.com/interactive/2012/08/01/business/01citi-doc.html"><span class="icon document">Document</span>: Securities and Exchange Commission v. Brian H. Stoker</a><br />
</span></p>
</div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .ru-story -->
<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">One Rule Regulators Are Rounding On <span class="divider">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span></span><!-- end .title --> Is a new requirement that banks need to have a stockpile of cash and high-quality, easy-to-sell assets to meet withdrawals in the event of a market panic making it harder for banks to fund themselves?<br /><span class="elsewhere"><a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2012/07/31/one-rule-regulators-are-rounding-on/">DealBook &#187;</a></span></p>
</div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .ru-story -->
<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">Regulator Opposes Plan to Ease Housing Debt <span class="divider">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span></span><!-- end .title --> After a study showed that taxpayers might save money if Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac were to offer debt forgiveness to borrowers, the director of the Federal Housing Finance Agency said his agency would not let such a program take place, The New York Times reports.<br /><span class="elsewhere"><a href="//www.nytimes.com/2012/08/01/business/us-agency-bars-fannie-and-freddie-from-reducing-principal.html?ref=todayspaper"> NEW YORK TIMES </a></span></p>
</div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .ru-story -->
<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">MF Global Trustee Expects Customers to Be Made Whole <span class="divider">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span></span><!-- end .title --> Louis J. Freeh, the trustee for MF Global Holdings, said in testimony prepared for a Senate committee that he believed customers of the bankrupt brokerage firm would recoup their money, Bloomberg News reports.<br /><span class="elsewhere"><a href="//www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-01/mf-global-customers-will-be-made-whole-freeh-says.html"> BLOOMBERG NEWS </a></span></p>
</div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .ru-story -->
<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">S.E.C. Calls for Reforms of Municipal Bond Market <span class="divider">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span></span><!-- end .title --> The Securities and Exchange Commission urged broad reforms of the market where cities raise money, but noted that it could not make the changes happen without an act of Congress, The New York Times reports.<br /><span class="elsewhere"><a href="//www.nytimes.com/2012/08/01/business/sec-urges-reforms-of-municipal-bond-market.html?ref=todayspaper"> NEW YORK TIMES </a></span></p>
</div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .ru-story -->
<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">Olympus Sued by Shareholder Over Loss <span class="divider">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span></span><!-- end .title --> Terumo Corporation, a Japanese medical device maker, is demanding to be compensated for a loss on its Olympus shares, Olympus said, according to Reuters.<br /><span class="elsewhere"><a href="//www.nytimes.com/reuters/2012/08/01/technology/01reuters-terumo-olympus-suit.html?src=busln"> REUTERS </a></span></p>
</div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .ru-story -->
<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">2 Poker Sites Agree to Give Up Millions <span class="divider">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span></span><!-- end .title --> Federal prosecutors said PokerStars and Full Tilt Poker agreed to settle money laundering and fraud charges, The New York Times reports.<br /><span class="elsewhere"><a href="//www.nytimes.com/2012/08/01/business/2-poker-sites-will-forfeit-731-million.html?ref=todayspaper"> NEW YORK TIMES </a></span></p>
</div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .ru-story --></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .ru-top-story -->
</div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .round-up -->
